name: Empanadas Cafe
address: 56-27 Van Doren St, Corona, NY 11368, USA

reviews.text: Let me tell you something if you wanna find the best empanadas in New York City. This is the place 100% recommended.
The food is affordable and prepared fresh per order. Great place for a quick lunch. The one change I would make is more seasoning since I personally prefer heavy spices.

Great place to get fresh empanadas but the only gripe that I have is that they are extremely cheap when it comes to the sauces. I ordered over 7 empenadas and only recieved 2 small sauce cups. The empenadas are already expensive so getting extra cups of sauce that are worth less than 10 cents shouldn't be a hassle.
Great place! My go to at work!!

I've had this place occasionally over the years, and the empanadas are always great. Some of the best I've had. The bacon egg and cheese one is great. I personally love the corn flour based ones, they have such a great crispy/chewy crust. Generous fillings. They must make these to order because even after I ordered it was about a ten minute wait for 4 empanadas, so be aware.

Empanadas Cafe in Corona is a true Queens treasure! ü•ü With dozens of fillings and three types of dough‚Äîwhite, corn, and whole grain‚Äîevery bite is fresh, authentic, and packed with flavor. We came here after a visit from the Queens Zoo and enjoyed our first visit here! It's too bad there are so tables to sit at, just a couple side benches and a tall table. Oh well, we liked the flour ones the best, the beef is a classic, and my fave, the ham and cheese reminded me of too much of a hot pocket, but we enjoyed the chicken/potato, and sweet plantains. Took like 45min to get our empanadas. 3 total and 1 coffee. And price was a little overpriced for empanadas. The service to public is not very kind. Be ready to wait!!!!!

I'm not very impressed. The cheese empanada was sad. Hardly any cheese at all. The beef one was filled right, but the taste was nothing out of this world. Ham & cheese and beef & potato were OK. We ordered 7 empanadas and got 3 sauces. 1 sauce for every 2 empanadas, I guess the 7th empanada didn't count for extra sauce, so we had to pay an extra dollar. Also, at $26, I found it to be a bit expensive for empanadas, especially when you have to stand on the street to eat them.

Empanadas Cafe has been on our bucket list for a while. It came to my mind this morning randomly and decided to give it a try to fulfill my craving. We got 6 empanadas with different flavors across different layers.

There are 4 different flours: Corn, White Corn, White and Whole Grain. I personally love the thin & crispy corn flour and my roommate preferred the classic white flour. They serve various filling options and we had difficulty deciding what to buy. Our favorites were the flavorful Breakfast and refreshing Hawaiian.

This little spot packs a punch with good food. We ordered the chicken empanadas and the beef potatoes with a coffee. Chicken was good yet the beef is by far the best. The green sauce tasted so fresh and wasn‚Äôt too spicy. The coffee was decent yet I can‚Äôt fault them for that with the food that good. I have to say with how small that location is they have figured out a way to have a place for more than just a few people to eat with standing tables and benches. Lastly, the staff is super friendly. I don‚Äôt speak Spanish and they were able to work with me. They have a huge amount of pride for Queens and appreciated my Queens shirt I was reppin.

4/1/22: Excellent empanadas. They take 10 to 20 minutes to cook after you order, but it's worth the wait. The crust is perfectly crispy and flaky. And they include a fresh made green hot sauce (not from a bottle). Had the plantain and cheese (4.75*), jalapeno and cheese (4.75*), Nutella and banana (4.5*), and the pork chicharron (4.0*, the only one I didn't love, I was expecting some of the crispy chicharron inside, but it's all soft, wouldn't order this one again as they've got so many other great ones).  Update: Came back the same day to order more: Corn Flour Shredded Beef and Potato (4.5*), Corn Flour Ground Beef and Cheese (4.5*), Whole Grain Chicken and Cheese (4.5*), Corn Flour Chicken and Potato (4.25*), White Flour Beef (4.25*), Corn Flour Broccoli and Cheese (4*, decent but boring, wouldn't order again), White Flour Spinach and Ricotta (4*, decent but boring, wouldn't order again), Corn Flour Codfish and Potato (3.5*, too fishy, wouldn't order again), White Flour Hawaiana (Ham, Cheese, Pineapple) (3.5*, too sweet, didn't like flavor, wouldn't order again).

Best empanadas I've ever had in life. I've had daydreams of the Hawaiian one for the past two days since I've had it. Spicy green sauce is an awesome compliment for any of the empanadas on the menu. Parking is difficult as the location is on the corner of a busy street.

Had urge for empanadas and tried this spot. The selections may change regularly as i read reviews and some empanadas were not available when I went there. Location is at a corner and parking is hard to find. Alternative side parking is in effect some days and I saw tickets on cars around the place. I ordered at the window and 15 minutes later they called me. I ordered 3 different types and they were labeled correctly and more importantly were delicious. Staff was friendly. There is no outdoor seating just a table and stand to stand and eat. This is a pure takeout spot.  I would recommend it if you have a hankering for empanadas.  Green sauce is a must.

The empanadas and this little spot are remarkable. Order on the phone in advance or at the window. They come in three shell types: corn, wheat, and whole grain. All are good, but the hearty whole grain is particularly special, and uncommon.‚Ä¶

Trek to Queens to checkout Empanadas Cafe. Upon arrival the ordering process is a bit confusing and you have to flag a staffer or ring the bell to get their attention. The establishment doesn‚Äôt allow entry and you must order from a window which makes the experience a bit impersonal.

You order and wait until your name is called. Once the order is ready and your name is called you can then make payment which I found a bit odd.

The empanadas were overall really good. I enjoyed the empanadas de Ma√≠z more than the other.

Their outdoor space is not suited for eating and oddly placed tables on an active sidewalk is not ideal. I recommend heading to the park which is relatively close by car or by foot.

Empanadas, different place..for a fast snack,or quick lunch, very good Empanadas, comes in corn or wheat, delicious.

I enjoy the delicious fish with potato and the traditional meat, it's  right on the spot freshly made, they have a whole different type of empanadas for every taste at a great price,the staff are great also don't forget the drinks.

This is by far my favorite empanada place! They make the best white flour mix vegetable empanada ever! They have a variety of fillings you can choose from with 3 different flour types you can choose from. Staff is very friendly and helpful especially if you don't speak Spanish like myself. Been going here for a few years - worth a try if you're in the area!

EDIT: got 10 mixed vegetable empanadas and took a bite into my first empanada and it was not a mixed vegetable empanada, instead it was a ham and cheese empanada and being vegan that's no bueno for me. The sweet plantain & mozzarella cheese was very interesting & soooo good ! I will definitely get that option again ! You guys got it ! I will definitely order again & check you guys out in person !

Prices same or better than other places. Friendly, fast service. No dine-in options, though there are a couple covered benches to the side. Order at RH window, then pay and pick up at LH window. Empanadas made fresh to order!
Small but an amazing place with best empanadas in Queens. It is a popular location and therefore expect it to be packed. The food is amazing and worth the wait.
